The paper deals with online optimization problems and stochastic control, which are typically studied in the machine learning and artificial intelligence communities (cs.LG, cs.AI). The use of predictions is a key aspect of the paper, which suggests that it may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the performance of online algorithms, which is a topic of interest in the data structures community (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes a specific algorithm, AFHC, which is a type of control algorithm, indicating that the paper may also be relevant to the systems and control community (cs.SY).
